cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with detecting and localizing anomalies in videos showing crowded scenes using fully convolutional neural networks. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves processing and analyzing multimedia data, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of feature representation and detection suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
